newsitem.title: USA: PSE to list Applied Extrusion, others.
newsitem.headline: PSE to list Applied Extrusion, others.

text.p: The Pacific Stock Exchange (PSE) said Monday it would list options on Applied Extrusion Technologies Inc and three other stocks on November 19.
The other options will be on Cooker Restaurant Corp, Furon Co and Inter-Tel Inc.
The PSE said Applied Extrusion options will have opening strike prices of 7-1/2, 10 and 12-1/2 and expiration months of December, January, March and June.
The options were allocated to pit representative James Burleson in the Octel Communications Corp trading crowd.
The Cooker options will open with strikes of 7-1/2, 10 and 12-1/2 and expirations of December, January, March and June.
The options were allocated to pit representatives Lynn Jolly and Kit Woolsey in the Lockheed Martin Corp trading crowd.
For Furon options, opening strikes will be at 17-1/2, 20 and 22-1/2 and will be available for December, January, March and June expiration. The options were also allocated to James Burleson.
Inter-Tel options will open with strikes of 15, 17-1/2 and 20 and expirations in December, January, April and July.
Market makers Michael Cole and Paul Roesler of Cole, Roesler & Associates were allocated the Inter-Tel options.
